President Muhammadu Buhari on Friday resumed juma’at prayer at the State House Mosque after the new guidelines on religious gathering were released. The Friday juma’at prayers at the mosque was suspended as a result of the outbreak of the dreaded Coronavirus pandemic in compliance with the social distancing order to contain the virus. But the Presidential Task Force on COVID-19 on Tuesday released new guidelines to ease the lockdown, saying worship centres will only be permitted to operate for a maximum of one hour each time they meet. <img class="size-full wp-image-1404278 aligncenter" src="https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/bubu1.jpg?resize=600%2C400&#038;ssl=1" alt="" width="600" height="400" srcset="https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/bubu1.jpg?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/bubu1.jpg?resize=300%2C200&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/bubu1.jpg?resize=58%2C39&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/bubu1.jpg?resize=260%2C173&amp;ssl=1 260w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/bubu1.jpg?resize=195%2C130&amp;ssl=1 195w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/bubu1.jpg?resize=115%2C77&amp;ssl=1 115w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> <img class="size-full wp-image-1404279 aligncenter" src="https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/BUBU2.jpg?resize=600%2C359&#038;ssl=1" alt="" width="600" height="359" srcset="https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/BUBU2.jpg?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/BUBU2.jpg?resize=300%2C180&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/BUBU2.jpg?resize=58%2C35&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/